All PTP event messages are time stamped on ingress.
The timestamp shall be the time at which the event message timestamp point passes the reference plane (boundary between PTP node and network).
This implementation generates event message timestamps at detection of SFD at MII. Use this parameter to correct appropriately.
Normally ingressLatency contains MAC sample delays + PHY receive delay + eventually PHY phase offsets
All PTP event messages are time stamped on egress.
The timestamp shall be the time at which the event message timestamp point passes the reference plane (boundary between PTP node and network).
This implementation generates event message timestamps at detection of SFD at MII. Use this parameter to correct appropriately.
Normally engressLatency contains MAC sample delays + PHY transmit delay
